  "text": "Vassiliou et al. demonstrated construct validity not only for the overall score, but also for each of the five GOALS items individually [CITATION_1] . Excellent internal consistency and inter-rater reliability were also demonstrated for the five-item global rating scale. Although the VAS did demonstrate construct validity, inter-rater reliability was weak and we feel that it does not add benefit to the five-item global rating scale. It is still included at the bottom of the rating scale; however, most studies published since the original in 2004 do not utilize the VAS.",
